  "text": "As long as modern sector workers have bargaining power that is derived from their ability to shut down production, wages don't fall to clear the urban labor market. [CITATION_1] . If wage differential between the modern and traditional sectors is sufficiently low, then the modern sector will grow and the traditional sector will decline. Eventually, the share of workers in the traditional sector will fall enough such that q(l) and w will rise. But if the wage differential is too high, the modern sector will stagnate or contract and development will not occur.",
